Citations
Date: 15/5/1945
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 513
Edition:
Quote: The types of spreader boards in use are many and varied, some being more efficient than others. ..In this case the spreader board is 18in. to 24in. wide and 6 ft.long. The manure falls into this box and thus finds it way out through the opening between the front of the box and the spreader board ...
